# Subagent Usage

- Use subagents for broad multi-area exploration or when independent investigations can run in parallel.
- Do not use subagents for single-file targeted edits or narrow symbol lookups.
- Prefer a single direct agent flow for small, local feature changes.
- For large refactors, gather context first, then execute in incremental, verifiable steps.
- Preserve current behavior and validate each increment with build/tests before moving on.
